# Silid Next.js structure

If `docs/PROJECT-STRUCTURE.md` exists, read it first. When unsure about Next.js 16 APIs, read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` (this stack differs from older Next.js).

**Stack:** Next.js 16 App Router · React 19 · Tailwind 4 · NextAuth v5 (`auth.ts`) · MySQL + Drizzle · Bun · `proxy.ts` (not middleware) for `/dashboard/*`

## Where code goes

| Path | Role |
| ---- | ---- |
| `app/dashboard/<feature>/queries.ts` | Server reads + `requireDashboardAccess()` |
| `app/dashboard/<feature>/actions.ts` | Server writes (`"use server"`) |
| `app/actions.ts` | Auth-guarded `createXAction()` factories |
| `db/usecase/` → `service/` → `controller/` → `api-modules/` | DB layers (never from pages) |
| `components/ui/` · `molecules/` · `organisms/` | shadcn primitives → page sections |

## Decision tree

- Static UI → Server Component `page.tsx`
- Forms/hooks/events → `"use client"` components
- Read data → `queries.ts` (+ optional `cached-actions.ts`)
- Write data → `actions.ts` with validation + `revalidatePath`
- Touch DB → usecase → service → controller → `createXModule()`

## Hard rules

1. Never import usecases from pages/components — use `createXModule()` or `createXAction()`.
2. `await searchParams` in pages/layouts (it is a Promise in Next.js 16).
3. `requireDashboardAccess()` in queries; owner-only → `requireOwnerAccess()`.
4. Mutations return `{ success, message }`.
5. Client mutations: `useTransition` + server action.
6. Prefer Server Actions + queries over new REST routes for dashboard UI.
7. Match existing naming in the domain you touch (`get<Entities>()`, `create<Domain>Module()`, `<verb><Entity>Action()`).

## New feature checklist

Types in `lib/types/` → DB layers → `createXAction()` in `app/actions.ts` → `page.tsx` + `queries.ts` + `actions.ts` → organism if interactive → nav in `admin-shell.tsx` if new section.
